Sprint Review 
a. What did you learn from doing our first sprint?
    The first sprint taught us the importance of communication and planning. It was through group meetings and constant communication that we worked together to get to where we are today. Our planning and ability to discuss what was going on at each of our tasks throughout all steps of the process was great.
b. What did go well? Why?
    Collaboration and planning was something that went well for us during this first sprint. Everyone was clear on what work was theirs to complete, and for the most part, everyone was communicating and checking in on the group with status updates.
c. What didn’t go well? Why not?
    Nothing didn't go well, but we could've gotten started on our respective tasks slightly earlier, as some of the tasks ended up feeling larger, and longer than we initially anticipated.
d. How can you make things better next time?
    For our next sprint, we are going to put extra emphasis on breaking the tasks down to smaller pieces, as this is the main characteristic and goal of the Agile framework, and will help us stay on top of deadlines, and avoid falling behind schedule.
e. Are you satisfied with what you already completed?
    Yes, we are satisfied with what we have already completed up until this point. We feel good about where we are in the overall process and are excited to continue working!
f. Which group was invited? What are your observations/notes? Everybody was present?
    We invited Group 7. Everybody was present and we thought their sprint looked very well done. They had great work and their feedback was helpful for us.